Rhubarb Meringue Pie

tasteofhome.com8 servings.50min1h 5min1h 55min

My husband’s grandmother was an excellent cook, but she didn’t always share her secrets. Luckily, we have her rhubarb pie recipe. I added one of my favorite crusts and a never-fail meringue. —Elaine Sampson, Colesburg, Iowa

Pastry

  • 90 g all-purpose flour
  • 2 g salt
  • 2 g sugar
  • 60 g butter
  • 1 beaten large egg, room temperature
  • 2 ml white vinegar
  • 15-22 ml cold water

FILLING:

  • 360 g chopped fresh or frozen rhubarb
  • 200 g sugar
  • 36 g flour
  • Dash of salt
  • 3 large egg yolks
  • 240 ml heavy whipping cream

MERINGUE:

  • 20 g plus 70 g sugar, divided total 90 g
  • 8 g cornstarch
  • 80 ml water
  • 3 large egg whites, room temperature
  • 1 g cream of tartar replace with 5 drips lemon juice
  1. In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and sugar; cut in shortening until crumbly.
  2. Combine egg and vinegar; sprinkle over crumb mixture. Gradually add water, tossing with a fork until a ball forms. Cover and chill for 1 hour or until easy to handle.
  3. On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough and place in a cake tin. Place rhubarb in crust.
  4. Whisk the sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks and cream; pour over rhubarb.
  5. Bake at 180°C until filling is set and the pie jiggles when gently shaken, 50-60 minutes.
  6. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, combine 20 g sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water.
  7. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; cook until thickened, 1-2 minutes.
  8. Cool to room temperature.
  9. In a small bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy. Add cornstarch mixture; beat on high until soft peaks form.
  10. Gradually beat in remaining sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, on high until stiff glossy peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
  11. Spread evenly over hot filling, sealing edges to crust. Bake until meringue is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
  12. Cool on a wire rack for 1 hour. Store in the refrigerator.
